{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2e8-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–31"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"460l–31"},"text":"§ 460l–31.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Findings","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Congress finds and declares the following:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2e9-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–31/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There is a Federal responsibility to provide opportunities for public recreation at Federal water projects.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2ea-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–31/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Some provisions of the Federal Water Project Recreation Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s460"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 460","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–12 et seq.] are outdated because of increases in demand for outdoor recreation and changes in the economic climate for recreation managing entities."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2eb-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–31/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Provisions of such Act relating to non-Federal responsibility for all costs of operation, maintenance, and replacement of recreation facilities result in an unfair burden, especially in cases where the facilities are old or underdesigned.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2ec-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–31/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Provisions of such Act that limit the Federal share of recreation facility development at water projects completed before 1965 to $100,000 preclude a responsible Federal share in providing adequate opportunities for safe outdoor recreation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2ed-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–31/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" There should be Federal authority to expand existing recreation facilities to meet public demand, in partnership with non-Federal interests.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2ee-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–31/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Nothing in this part changes the responsibility of the Bureau to meet the purposes for which Federal Reclamation projects were initially authorized and constructed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2ef-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s460l–31/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" It is therefore in the best interest of the people of this Nation to amend the Federal Water Project Recreation Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s460"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 460","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–12 et seq.] to remove outdated restrictions and authorize the Secretary of the Interior to undertake specific measures for the management of Reclamation lands."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id77c2c2f0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/575/tXXVIII/s2802"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–575, title XXVIII, § 2802","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4690"},"text":"106 Stat. 4690","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id77c2c2f1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id77c2c2f2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id77c2c2f3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal Water Project Recreation Act, referred to in pars. (2) to (4) and (7), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/89/72"},"text":"Pub. L. 89–72","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1965-07-09"},"text":"July 9, 1965","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/79/213"},"text":"79 Stat. 213","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to part C (§ 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–12 et seq.) of this subchapter. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under section 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–12 of this title and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This part, referred to in par. (6), was in the original “this title”, meaning title XXVIII of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/575"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–575","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4690"},"text":"106 Stat. 4690","children":[],"tail":", which enacted sections 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–31 to 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–34 of this title and amended sections 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–13 to 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–15 and 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–18 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id77c2c2f4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id77c2c2f5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/575/tXXVIII/s2801"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–575, title XXVIII, § 2801","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4690"},"text":"106 Stat. 4690","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/102/575/tXXVIII/s2801"},"text":"“This title [enacting this part and amending sections 460","children":[{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–13 to 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–15 and 460"},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"l","children":[],"tail":"–18 of this title] may be cited as the ‘Reclamation Recreation Management Act of 1992’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
